{"article_id":"1jz79zSAAaDiD7pn","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The U.S. Supreme Court hears arguments Tuesday in a highly anticipated set of cases","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that threatens the legal status of some 700,000 young immigrants","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"- often called DREAMers -","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"who were brought to the U.S. illegally as children .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"It 's a program","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that President Trump tried to rescind seven months after taking office ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"only to have the lower courts block his action .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"In 2012 , President Barack Obama put the program in place","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"to temporarily protect these young people from deportation .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"If you were in school ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"were a high school graduate ,","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"or had been honorably discharged from the military ,","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"and if you passed a background check ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"you were eligible for temporary legal status and a work permit , renewable every two years .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"The program is formally known as the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals , or DACA .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"President Trump , from the beginning , seemed conflicted about DACA ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"caught between the mass deportations","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"he promised his political base during the campaign","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"and his admiration for","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"what so many of the DREAMers have accomplished .","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"These DACA recipients ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"who come from around the world ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"have become teachers , psychologists , business owners and doctors .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Their successes illustrate the reason","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"that Republicans and Democrats in Congress tried to work out a DACA deal","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that Trump would sign in 2017 .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"`` Rest easy , ''","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Trump told the DREAMers in an April 2017 interview with The Associated Press .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"But he `` kept waffling back and forth over what he would be willing to accept ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"and would n't be willing to accept , '' in terms of a DACA deal ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"says Julie Hirschfeld Davis , co-author of Border Wars and congressional editor for The New York Times .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"At the end of the day , Trump 's indecision was so frustrating for Senate Republican leaders","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"that they worked out a compromise with Democrats on their own .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Just hours before the deal was to come up for a vote on the Senate floor , however ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"the administration branded it unacceptable in a midnight press release ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"according to Davis .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Shortly thereafter , then-Attorney General Jeff Sessions announced","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"that the DACA program would end","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"because ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"he said ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"it was illegal and unconstitutional to begin with .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` They are dead wrong","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"when they say","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"that the DACA program","depth":14},{"id":44,"text":"adopted by the Obama administration","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"was illegal , ''","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"says Ted Olson ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"who served as solicitor general in the George W. Bush administration","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"and is representing DACA plaintiffs in the Supreme Court .","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"Olson points to programs similar to DACA","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"that were put in place by every other president","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"dating back to Dwight Eisenhower .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"These programs granted temporary legal status , for instance , to 600,000 Cubans in the 1950s and '60s and 1.5 million other undocumented immigrants under another program in the Reagan and George H.W . Bush administrations .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Janet Napolitano was secretary at the Department Homeland Security","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"when DACA was created .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"`` Not only is there a long history","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"of deferring action for particular groups under the immigration laws , ''","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"says Napolitano ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"`` but there 's the whole concept of prosecutorial discretion ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"which gives the executive branch the authority","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"to make decisions","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"about who is going to feel the full brunt of the federal government in an enforcement proceeding , versus not . '' `","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"` The Supreme Court has long recognized","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"that there may be a line between prosecutorial discretion , not enforcing the law in every instance ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"and a complete suspension of the law , ''","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"counters John Eastman , a constitutional law professor at Chapman University","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"who has filed a brief","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"siding with the Trump administration in the DACA case .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Eastman maintains","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"that DACA is different from other , similar programs in prior administrations ,","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"citing DACA recipients ' benefits","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"- including work authorization , Social Security benefits and tax credits on tax returns -","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"as different from prior administrations .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"Napolitano replies","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"that granting temporary legal status to DACA recipients enables them to work ,","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"and","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"when they work ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"they must pay into Social Security","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"and pay taxes .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Indeed , government statistics indicate","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"that some 91 % of DACA recipients have jobs ,","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"allowing them to support their families","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"and generating , over a 10-year period , nearly $ 60 billion in federal tax revenue","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"that the government stands to lose","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"if the DACA program is abolished .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"Napolitano is no longer DHS secretary .","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"She is the president of the giant University of California system ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"including 1,700 students with DACA status .","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"And in that capacity , she is challenging Trump 's revocation of the DACA program as so arbitrary and unsupported by stated reasons and data","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"that the revocation is itself illegal .","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"`` If they had done a full policy review","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"and had set forth all their reasons","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"and demonstrated","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that they had weighed the pros and cons","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"and just came to a different conclusion ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"they might be able to prevail in this case , ''","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"says Napolitano .","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"`` But they did n't do that .","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"Instead they just simply issued basically a one-sentence order","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"that said","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"since DACA is illegal","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"or was illegal ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"we 're going to undo it . ''","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Sometimes lost in all the legal discussion are the people","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"whose lives will be affected by the Supreme Court 's decision in the DACA case .","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"DACA recipient Mitchell Santos Toledo ,","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"brought to the U.S.","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"when he was 2","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"and now in his last year at Harvard Law School ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"remembers crying","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"when he received his Social Security card .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"`` This is home for us .","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"It 's not a place","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"I call home .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"It is home , ''","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"he says .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"A first-of-its-kind video friend of the court brief","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"filed by United We Dream","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"seeks to highlight other DACA stories .","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"`` We got DACA","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"and it 's like we got wings .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"I am a mom , a wife and a business owner , ''","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"says Angelica Villalobos ,","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"who owns an auto repair shop .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"`` I worked on a project","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"that won two Grammys , ``","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"says Emmanuel A .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"`` I did some fieldwork","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"picking strawberries .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"I decided to become a teacher","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"so that students could have that role model , ''","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"says Maricruz R .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"Public support for DACA is illustrated by a distinct imbalance in friend of the court briefs","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"filed in the case .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"Six have been filed","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"supporting the administration 's position .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"They include briefs","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"filed by conservative organizations and individuals","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"and a brief","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"filed by 12 Republican-dominated states .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"A total of 35 briefs have been filed in support of DACA .","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"Among them are briefs","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"filed by higher education associations , health professionals and even briefs","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"filed by more than 145 corporations and business organizations","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"arguing","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"if the court were to side with the Trump administration","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"and abolish DACA ,","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"their companies and industries would be significantly disrupted .","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"A decision on DACA is expected by summer ,","depth":3},{"id":150,"text":"just as the 2020 election is kicking into high gear .","depth":3},{"id":151,"text":"Republicans in Congress may be hoping","depth":4},{"id":152,"text":"that the high court will let them off the hook","depth":5},{"id":153,"text":"and rule in favor of DACA .","depth":5},{"id":154,"text":"Whether the current Supreme Court ,","depth":5},{"id":155,"text":"dominated by conservative justices","depth":6},{"id":156,"text":"inclined to defer to presidential power ,","depth":6},{"id":157,"text":"fulfills those hopes , however , remains to be seen .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":315,"left":306,"right":314,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":242,"right":305,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":210,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"le